lec 160:-
click() :- for clicking
$("button").click(function(){
	$(this).css("background","pink")
});

lec 161:-
keypress() :- anytime when a key is pressed between up an down.
keydown() :- Right after the key is down.
keyup() :- fired after releasing a key.
If there is a text input adn someone clicks shift + a. keydown fire when shift and a
the keypress will give "A".
which referes to the code of the key which is pressed
("input").keypress(function(event){
	if(event.which === 13){
	alert("Pressed enter");
	}
});

lec 162:-
on();
$("h1").on("mouseenter", function(){
	$(this).css("color","puruple")
});
mouseenter is hover
mouseleave is opposite enter
on click is better than click. As on click will add click for all future elements.

lec 163:-
fadeOut();
$("button").on("click", function(){
$('div').fadeOut(1000, function(){
	$(this).remove(); //remove faded elements
});
});
// there is also fadeIn(); and fadeToggle(500);
